  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A diet rich in whole grain is inversely associated with cardiovascular disease risk and this
      benefit could be partly attributed to the phenolic acid content of whole grains. The exact
      absorption, metabolism and excretion of whole grain phenolic acids, however, is not fully
      understood. In a small human intervention trial, the investigators will investigate to what
      extent phenolic acids from whole grain oats are absorbed, excreted in urine and how they are
      metabolised.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
